The luxury fashion industry is increasingly adopting sustainability measures, focusing on transparent sourcing, sustainable materials, and ethical production practices. Brands like Gucci and Burberry are leading efforts to reduce environmental impacts, yet challenges such as scalability and consumer expectations remain prominent. Despite numerous attempts to gather specific statistics on the environmental impact and innovative practices, access to recent data has been limited. It is recommended that luxury fashion brands implement circular economy models, enhance supply chain transparency, and collaborate with NGOs to advance their sustainability initiatives.